==English==
===Etymology===
Perhaps from being first made by a Ruby Neenish in the Australian town of [[w:Grong Grong, New South Wales|Grong Grong, New South Wales]] circa 1913.  Or perhaps of German or Vienese origin as ''nienich''.  (Reference: Australian National University OzWords October 1996 [http://www.anu.edu.au/andc/ozwords/October_96/5._aussie_words.htm].)
===Noun===
'''neenish [[tart]]'''
# A small [[tart]] with a [[pastry]] base, [[gelatine]]-set [[cream]] filling, and covered with [[icing]] in two colours, half and half.
===Synonyms===
* [[nienich tart]]
